MATERIAL AND LOCALITY. — see 
<tableCitation id="820A68874466FFC939B13AADFD932B1B" box="[435,513,1535,1559]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="3.[113,122,219,237]" captionText="TABLE 1. — Localities and stratigraphy of serpulid species from Jurassic-Cretaceous seeps and background sediments from Svalbard. Abbreviations: Fm, Formation; spec., specimen." pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Table 1.</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="87920EB74466FFC938733918FBAC28E9" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" type="description">
<paragraph id="CF375D3C4466FFC938733918FE902B6E" blockId="4.[112,646,1610,1700]" box="[113,258,1610,1636]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF375D3C4466FFC93873393BFD142BA8" blockId="4.[112,646,1610,1700]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Tubes curved, with circular cross section.Tube wall rather thick, 0.7 mm at tube diameter 3.2 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF375D3C4466FFC93AA73A7FFBAC28E9" blockId="4.[675,1209,1325,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
Entire tube covered with extremely regular fine perpendicular rings, 8 to 9 per 
<quantity id="0870F0D94466FFC93BFC3A1EFBAC286B" box="[1022,1086,1356,1383]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
at tube diameter of 5.0 mm. Several weakly developed thin, but regularly shaped ampullacea-type peristomes present, about 0.5mm wide.Tube double-layered, with chevron-shaped growth lamellae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="87920EB74466FFC83AA73959FE582CBC" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="532" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CF375D3C4466FFC83AA73959FE582CBC" blockId="4.[674,1210,1547,1700]" lastBlockId="5.[111,647,216,432]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="532" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
DISCUSSION ffle specimens are assigned to? 
<taxonomicName id="088826BF4466FFC93BF53979FBF62B48" authorityName="Stolley" authorityYear="1912" box="[1015,1124,1578,1604]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Ditrupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="decorata">
<emphasis id="FDFC812E4466FFC93BF53979FBF62B48" box="[1015,1124,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">P. decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to their characteristic fine perpendicular tube ornamentation.? 
<taxonomicName id="088826BF4466FFC93AE1393BFC3B2B8F" baseAuthorityName="Stolley" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[739,937,1641,1667]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="decorata">
<emphasis id="FDFC812E4466FFC93AE1393BFC3B2B8F" box="[739,937,1641,1667]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Pyrgopolon decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a serpulid because of the chevron-shaped growth lamellae, and we tentatively ascribe this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="088826BF4467FFC839AC3F8AFD882DFE" authorityName="de Montfort" authorityYear="1808" box="[430,538,216,242]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FDFC812E4467FFC839AC3F8AFD882DFE" box="[430,538,216,242]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">Pyrgopolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its relatively thick walled and large tubes.? 
<taxonomicName id="088826BF4467FFC83A1A3FA5FF562C3D" baseAuthorityName="Stolley" baseAuthorityYear="1912" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="decorata">
<emphasis id="FDFC812E4467FFC83A1A3FA5FF562C3D" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">Pyrgopolon decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from? 
<taxonomicName id="088826BF4467FFC839543E4AFD962C3D" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Lundgren" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[342,516,279,305]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="nodulosum">
<emphasis id="FDFC812E4467FFC839543E4AFEFB2C3D" box="[342,361,280,305]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">P.</emphasis>
aff. 
<emphasis id="FDFC812E4467FFC839943E45FD962C3D" box="[406,516,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">nodulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of fine regular perpendicular ornamentation.? 
<taxonomicName id="088826BF4467FFC838783E04FED62C7C" baseAuthorityName="Stolley" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[122,324,342,368]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="decorata">
<emphasis id="FDFC812E4467FFC838783E04FED62C7C" box="[122,324,342,368]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">Pyrgopolon decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from? 
<taxonomicName id="088826BF4467FFC839DB3E04FD142C7D" box="[473,646,342,369]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="5" pageNumber="532" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undefined-A">
<emphasis id="FDFC812E4467FFC839DB3E04FDDA2C7C" box="[473,584,342,368]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="532">Pyrgopolon</emphasis>
sp. A
</taxonomicName>
in having fine regular perpendicular ornamentation and ampullacea-type peristomes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
